{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}
'''Hygroreception''' is the ability to detect changes in the [[moisture]] and [[humidity]] content of an [[Environment (biophysical)|environment]]. It is a [[sense]] that is not present in [[human]]s. Some [[insect]]s have this sense.<ref name="Rivers Dahlem 2014 p. 157">{{cite book | last=Rivers | first=D.B. | last2=Dahlem | first2=G.A. | title=The Science of Forensic Entomology | publisher=Wiley | series=EBL-Schweitzer | year=2014 | isbn=978-1-119-94036-4 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NgMiAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA157 | access-date=20 October 2018 | page=157}}</ref> The structure responsible for this sense is a hygroreceptor.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Enjin |first=Anders |last2=Zaharieva |first2=Emanuela E. |last3=Frank |first3=Dominic D. |last4=Mansourian |first4=Suzan |last5=Suh |first5=Greg S. B. |last6=Gallio |first6=Marco |last7=Stensmyr |first7=Marcus C. |title=Humidity Sensing in Drosophila |url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0960982216302597 |journal=Current Biology |doi=10.1016/j.cub.2016.03.049 |volume=26 |pages=1352–1358 |pmid=27161501}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last=Tichy |first=Harald |last2=Kallina |first2=Wolfgang |date=16 January 2013 |title=The Evaporative Function of Cockroach Hygroreceptors |url=http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0053998 |journal=PLOS ONE |volume=8 |issue=1 |pages=e53998 |doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0053998 |issn=1932-6203 |pmc=3546976 |pmid=23342058}}</ref>

